### 12. CRITICAL ISSUES FOR TRADING BOT

For a **live trading bot**, the frontend is:
**Strong Points:**

- ✅ Real-time WebSocket updates (risk alerts, trades, signals, regime changes)
- ✅ Kill switch controls (pause trading, rebalance, force liquidate)
- ✅ Risk metrics display (drawdown, VaR, volatility, Sharpe)
- ✅ Manual trade override capability
- ✅ System health monitoring (7 modules tracked)
- ✅ Configuration UI (mode switching, weights, kill switches, ETF universe)
- ✅ Trade execution log with slippage tracking
  **Critical Weaknesses:**
- ❌ **No live account balance/cash display** — only portfolio value from last signal
- ❌ **No open orders display** — only filled trades shown
- ❌ **No stop-loss/take-profit management UI** — trades are fire-and-forget
- ❌ **No margin/buying power indicators** (for Alpaca)
- ❌ **No correlation/regime transition early warning** — charts are historical only
- ❌ **No sentiment/news context** — factors exist but not visualized
- ⚠️ **Backtest infrastructure unclear** — may not be functional for tuning live strategy
- ⚠️ **MT5 support not exposed** — backend ready but no UI
  **For Production Go-Live:**

1. Implement live account status panel (cash, buying power, margin level)
2. Build open orders tracker (pending orders with cancel button)
3. Add order management UI (set/update stop-loss, take-profit)
4. Implement correlation quadrant warning (if correlation spikes → alert)
5. Add sentiment/news feed visualization
6. Test backtest functionality end-to-end
7. Build MT5 account connection + position sync UI

